      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHOWMETHETANLINES NZ (10) resumes off the NSW Derby series where won his heat before a midfield finish in the final. May need some luck from this barrier but he races well fresh with two wins and a placing from three attempts and a couple of nice trials suggest he is in good order. FIRE AND PASSION (4) continued a string of top-two finishes when he led and stuck on behind a good filly last week. Easy winner of the Breeders Classic at Albion Park prior and should push forward from this draw. BEROCCA BERNIE (2) has been good from tough barriers in three Albion Park starts since arriving from NSW. Won easily from wider last month and has placed from the back row in both outings since. Should get his chance from a more favourable draw. TIMMYTEO (1) has won two of three outings so far this time in, the latest from the back row at Albion Park. Won the only time he raced here and gets the ace draw. Former Kiwi NYMBAL NZ (9) draws on the back row but is the query at his Australian debut.",
